addApprover(address).details: Only callable by contract owner and before any challenge deadline

params.account: The address to be granted approver rights

params.challengeId: The ID of the challenge being submitted
params.nickname: The nickname of the player (optional if already set)
params.playerAddress: The address of the player submitting the challenge
params.points: Array of points earned for the challenge

params.initialOwner: The address that will own the contract

returns._0: points Array of points from the submission
tokenId The ID of the token, or revert if not found

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeApprover(address).details: Only callable by contract owner and before any challenge deadline

params.account: The address to remove approver rights from

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

approveSubmission(uint256,string,address.notice: Approve a player's challenge submission and mint an NFT

getChallengeId(uint256).notice: Get the challenge ID associated with a token

getPoints(uint256).notice: Get points for a specific token

getTokenForChallenge(address,uint256).notice: Get the token ID for a player's completed challenge

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns token URI by combining base URI with challenge ID and token ID
